On Escalation Ticket # 00414050 the new comment has been added: Krzysztof Staszalek:

Hi Support,
This seems to be natural behavior, especially now when current logs + old one processed after fixing vulnerability fix are processed.

On default view you see column "Date/Time(Client)" in chaotic order, but those logs are sorted out by "Date/Time(Server)" column not visible by default.
Please click on "Show/Hide Column" and enable "Date/Time(Server)", then you should be able see that this column has little purple arrow showing descent sorting. You can switch sorting to "Client" column and logs will be resorted.

Note1: If Server is still processing old logs - it will decrees performance of logs processing.
Note2: Sorting order option is not saved if admin leave this CAP report tab and will back to it later.




fyi @Cristian-Alexandru Halmajan @Andrew Siemasko @Sara Hall @Stacy Petruzzi @Jonathan Micheal Orford @Peter Rooney
